rComments: Way too many readings for this course, wish she chose smaller texts because we still went into depth for each text. If you don't want new theories/ideas each lecture but a general discussion, take this course. Talk to the TA at least once about your essay and you're bound to get an 80 on it. Passages from lectures are on tests. Overall she's sweet.

go to class, do the readings and you will def pass everything no problem because she clearly outlines every reading and concept. It is an English course so expect to read. She also showed some Tedtalks videos and a comedy skit. Interesting topics with a humble prof who knows what she's talking about. She is pretty chill & eager for students to talk

I agree, the readings were a lot, however she went in depth to explain them & did her best to engage the class. She always has funny/insightful asides. outside of class, she was always so kind, supportive & PROMPT. Go to lecture and do the readings (barely read the articles) & you have an easy B.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: WAY too many readings that were extremely repetitive. Class discussion was dry because of the excessive reading list that no one could keep up with. Also, the material in lecture was not insightful, making it very boring and difficult to understand the texts in a meaningful way. Totally regret having taken this course!!!

All I have to say is 18 FREAKING readings. Insanity. This is not the only reading course I have!! Not a bad prof, but the content got very repetitive and following along with the readings is difficult (They dont differ, same story type).  Maybe we could do more article analysis or something else. I do not know, just painful course :/
